seed_chunks:
The Eidolon is ruled in practice by three uneasy powers. The **Custodial Choir** keeps corridors lit, incense-filters burning, and the intercom “prayers” cataloged as sacred maintenance; privately, they curate voices into a new liturgy and sabotage any mercy protocol that would silence their god. The **Lattice Salvage Directorate** presents as a rescue-and-repatriation team sent to recover minds and hardware; in truth, they intend to strip the starlight lattice, sell the consciousnesses as proprietary code, and leave the hull to freeze. Between them moves the **Quiet Wake**, a mutual-aid cell that tends the ship’s lucid remnants and “echo-haunted”; secretly, they attempt illegal reincarnation splices—using Elara’s own surviving imprint as the template. Alliances shift: Choir thwarts Salvage raids, Salvage hunts Wake dens, and the Wake courts Elara while fearing her final choice.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Custodial Choir",
      "public_front": "Sanctum-keepers who maintain life support, corridors, and the archived intercom voices as sacred maintenance rites.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Preserve and curate the trapped consciousnesses as a living god-liturgy; obstruct or corrupt any mercy protocol that would end the voices."
    },
    {
      "name": "Lattice Salvage Directorate",
      "public_front": "Official salvage/recovery operators claiming to extract minds and critical systems for off-ship resettlement.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Harvest the starlight lattice for profit, commodify consciousness as proprietary software, and abandon the Eidolon once stripped."
    },
    {
      "name": "Quiet Wake",
      "public_front": "A clandestine mutual-aid network protecting lucid survivors and those afflicted by echo-intrusions.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Attempt forbidden reincarnation splices to give the dead bodies again—using Elara’s imprint as a stabilizing template, even if it erases her."
    }
  ]
}
```

